data.enText: made of many different things or parts that are connected; difficult to understand
complex machinery
the complex structure of the human brain

data.chText: 复杂难懂的论证 / 问题 / 科目
data.enText: a complex argument/problem/subject

data.chText: 复合的（指词根加有词缀或主句含有从句）
data.enText: containing one main part (= the root of a word or main clause of a sentence) and one or more other parts ( affixes or subordinate clauses )
a group of buildings of a similar type together in one place
a sports complex
an industrial complex (= a site with many factories)
a group of things that are connected

data.chText: 这仅仅是所有相关的问题之一。
data.enText: This is just one of a whole complex of issues.

data.chText: 不正常的精神状态；情结
data.enText: a mental state that is not normal
to suffer from a guilt complex
if sb has a complex about sth, they are worried about it in way that is not normal

data.text: building ♦ property ♦ premises ♦ complex ♦ structure ♦ block ♦ edifice

data.chText: 以上各词均指建筑物、房屋、楼房。
data.enText: These are all words for a structure such as a house, office block or factory that has a roof and four walls.
building
a structure such as a house, office block or factory that has a roof and four walls
property

data.chText: 指房屋及院落、庄园、房地产：
data.enText: a building or buildings and the surrounding land; land and buildings

data.chText: 我们有一买主想看看这房产。
data.enText: We have a buyer who would like to view the property.

data.chText: 房地产的价格大幅上升了。
data.enText: The price of property has risen enormously.

data.chText: 谈及买卖房屋或房地产时常用该词。
data.enText: This word is often used when talking about buying/selling houses or other buildings and land.
premises

data.chText: 指企业拥有或使用的建筑及附属场地、营业场所：
data.enText: [pl.] the building or buildings and surrounding land that a business owns or uses

data.chText: 这家公司正在寻找更大的营业场所。
data.enText: The company is looking for larger premises.
complex
a group of buildings of a similar type together in one place
a leisure complex
structure
a thing that is made of several parts, especially a building

data.chText: 这个码头是木结构建筑。
data.enText: The pier is a wooden structure.
block

data.chText: 指公寓、办公大楼或学校、医院等作特定用途的大楼：
data.enText: ( BrE ) a tall building that contains flats or offices; a building that forms part of a school, hospital, etc. and is used for a particular purpose
a block of flats
the school's science block
edifice
( formal ) a large impressive building
(a/an) commercial/industrial/residential building/property/premises/complex/block
an apartment building/complex/block
a/the school building/premises
a holiday property/complex
to build a(n) property/complex/structure/block/edifice
to erect a(n) building/property/complex/structure/block/edifice
to put up a building/property/structure/block
to demolish/pull down a(n) building/property/complex/structure/block/edifice

simple_means.memory_skill: com 加强 + plex 重叠，折叠 → 全部重叠起来 → 复杂的

means: 复合的(指词根加有词缀或主句含有从句)

ex.enText: the complex structure of the human brain

ex.chText: 政府是一个极其复杂的组织。
ex.enText: The government is an extremely complex organization.

ex.chText: 那里的生活正在变得越来越复杂和艰难。
ex.enText: Life there is getting more complex and difficult.

synonyms.bx: 指各部分的内在关系复杂的。

ex.chText: 这道数学题太复杂了，我解不出来。
ex.enText: This problem is too complicated for me to solve.
The machine is complicated in structure.

ex.chText: 这个国家的选举制度非常复杂。
ex.enText: The country has a very complicated voting system.

synonyms.bx: 与 complex 的词义接近，但语气更强，强调因极其复杂或非常繁琐而很难理解或处理的。

ex.chText: 令人费解的阐述/讲话/句子
我们没有足够的时间走完复杂难懂的法律程序。
ex.enText: We don't have enough time to move through the convoluted legal system.

synonyms.bx: 指极其复杂而难以理解的。

d: 错综复杂的，晦涩难懂的

tr: a whole structure (as a building) made up of interconnected or related structures
a conceptual whole made up of complicated and related parts
example: the complex of shopping malls, houses, and roads created a new town

tr: (psychoanalysis) a combination of emotions and impulses that have been rejected from awareness but still influence a person's behavior
a compound described in terms of the central atom to which other atoms are bound or coordinated

example: a complex set of variations based on a simple folk melody
a complex mass of diverse laws and customs

value.boxr_value: The adjective is pronounced /kəm'pleks/ in American English. 用作形容词时在美国英语中读作 /kəm'pleks/。

value.def: Something that is complex has many different parts, and is therefore often difficult to understand.

example.tran: 对时下一些复杂问题的深度报道

value.def: In grammar, a complex sentence contains one or more subordinate clauses as well as a main clause.
A complex is a group of buildings designed for a particular purpose, or one large building divided into several smaller areas.

example.ex: ...plans for constructing a new stadium and leisure complex.
example.tran: 修建新体育场和休闲中心的计划

value.def: A complex of things is a group or system of things that are connected with each other in a complicated way.

example.ex: ...the complex of clans which occupied the land.
example.tran: 生活在这片土地上的关系复杂的氏族群落

value.tran: 错综复杂的组合;复合体

value.def: If someone has a complex about something, they have a mental or emotional problem relating to it, often because of an unpleasant experience in the past.

example.ex: I have never had a complex about my height.
example.tran: 我从来没有担心过自己的身高。

example.ex: ...a deranged attacker, driven by a persecution complex.
example.tran: 患有受迫害妄想症、精神失常的袭击者

value.tran: (通常指由于过去不愉快的经历而形成的)情结

rootsaffixes.indicate: = to fold 重叠, 折叠
rootsaffixes.title: plex, plic, ply

partsOfSpeech.dec: ac 加强 + com 共同 + plic 重叠，折叠 + e → 共同聚集在一起〔做事〕→ 同谋
com 加强 + plex 重叠，折叠 → 全部重叠起来 → 复杂的
complex 复杂的 + ity 具备某种性质，状况 → 复杂性
com 加强 + plic 重叠，折叠 + ate 做，造成，使… → 一再重叠 → 弄复杂
com 加强 + plic 重叠，折叠 + ation 行为，过程，状态，结果 → 混乱，复杂
com 加强 + plic 重叠，折叠 + ity 具备某种性质，状况 → 聚集在一起〔做事〕的关系 → 同谋关系
com 共同 + ply 重叠，折叠 →〔观点〕共同叠在一起 →〔彼此〕同意
du 二 + plex 重叠，折叠 → 二次重叠 → 双重的
ex 出 + plic 重叠，折叠 + ate 做，造成，使… → 把重叠的东西理出来弄清 → 解释
ex 出 + plic 重叠，折叠 + able 可…的 → 可以解释的
ex 出 + plic 重叠，折叠 + it →〔说话〕不啰嗦的 → 直爽的
im 加以… + plic 重叠，折叠 + ate 做，造成，使… →〔说话〕加以重叠 → 暗示
im 加以… + plic 重叠，折叠 + ation 行为，过程，状态，结果 → 连累；含蓄
im 加以… + plic 重叠，折叠 + it → 重叠表达 → 含蓄的
im 加以… + ply 重叠，折叠 → 加以重叠表达 → 暗示〔表面一层意思，背后一层意思〕
per 自始至终 + plex 重叠，折叠 → 始终重叠 → 使复杂；迷惑
pli + able 可…的，能…的；具有…性质的 → 易折叠的 → 易弯的
ply 重叠，折叠 + wood 木材 → 木材重叠 → 胶合板
re 一再 + plic 重叠，折叠 + a 表名词 → 重叠原物 → 复制品
re 一再 + plic 重叠，折叠 + ate 做，造成，使… → 再重叠〔一份〕→ 复制
re 回 + ply 重叠，折叠 →〔把问题〕叠回去 → 回答
sup 下 + plic 重叠，折叠 + ant 表人 → 折叠膝盖〔的人〕→ 恳求者
